.TH DIAGFS 1 "2026-05" "BusyBox-Diag" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
diagfs \- Filesystem health checker
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B diagfs
[\fIPATH\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B diagfs
is a diagnostic tool used to quickly check disk space, inode usage, and file fragmentation on Linux mount points. It is part of the BusyBox-Diag project.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-all
Scan all mounted filesystems.
.TP
.BR \-\-real
Scan real filesystems only (effective only when combined with \-\-all).
.TP
.BR \-\-pseudo
Scan pseudo filesystems only (effective only when combined with \-\-all).
.TP
.BR \-\-output " " \fIraw|json|table\fR
Specify the output format. Default is \fItable\fR.
.TP
.BR \-\-color " " \fIauto|always|never\fR
Control colorized output.
.TP
.BR \-\-fiemap
Require FIEMAP support for fragmentation analysis.
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Show help message and exit.
.SH AUTHOR
Part of the BusyBox-Diag project.